----- Original Message ----
From: Frank Sumption &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt;
To: Group &lt;evp-itc@yahoogroups.com&gt;
Sent: Tuesday, March 25, 2008 8:49:12 AM
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Spiricom comparison

                 The Spiricom supposedly used 13 tone gnerators to simulate the tones of human speech, then transmitted that over a CB, or 29 mhz carrier so the spirits could modulate the tones. If I understood the small amount of reading I&#39;ve done on the system.  Curiously,  no ones seems to be able to get it to works, but, it seems no on can my box schematics to work either. 

 The &quot;RoboBox&quot; uses a speech sythesizer chip, which produce tones and modualtions that approximate human speech, but it also puts out the various other sound effects like R2-D2, and various chirps and whistles, as I don&#39;t program the chip for speech only. This first attempt is just accessing the Speakjet with  random pulses from the old random voltage generator I&#39;ve used in the boxes. I use an adapter to convert the white noise to random digital pusles that the Speakjet can process. 

 The spirits seem to use all the sounds and noise to make voices, so eliminating all ofthe noise might limit access to a certain range, or higher entities. 

 Frank-S


